# Git Summary
1. Clone or Pull: 	git clone URL | git pull
2. Create branch: 	git checkout -d <branch>
----- Changes ---------
3. Changes:		git status
4. Add: 		git add <file> or git add *
5. Commit:		git commit -m "<message>"
6. Push:		git push origin <branch>
----- Merge Request ---
List branches:		git branch
History:		git log --pretty=oneline
Switch: 		git checkout <branch>
Delete:			git branch -d <branch>
Diff:			git branch <source-branch> <target-branch>


-------------------------------------------------------
---------------------- DETAILS ------------------------

# Repository
New:       git init
Clone:     git clone username@host:/path/to/repository
Pull:      git pull
History:   git log --pretty=oneline

# Branches
List:			git branch
Create & Switch:    	git checkout -b <branch>
 - Create		git branch <branch>
 - Switch		git checkout <branch>
Delete     		git branch -d <branch>
Switch      		git checkout <branch> 
Diff       		git diff <source-branch> <target-branch>

# Add & remove Index
Status:    		git status
Add file:  		git add <file> | git add *
Remove:    		git rm <file>

# Commit & Push
Commit:    		git commit -u "message"
Push:      git push origin <branch>

# Merge & Tag
Merge     git merge <branch>
Tag       git tag <tag> <commit-ID>
